SupportingEvidence: Upregulation of collagen genes (COL3A1, COL1A2, COL1A1, COL6A3) suggests a mesenchymal phenotype, which is characteristic of embryonal subtype.
SPARC, a matricellular protein involved in tissue remodeling, is often upregulated in embryonal subtype.
VIM (Vimentin) is a marker of epithelial to mesenchymal transition, supporting the embryonal subtype.
SuggestedExperiments: Perform immunohistochemistry for COL1A1, COL1A2, and VIM to confirm the mesenchymal phenotype.
Investigate the presence of other embryonal subtype markers, such as AFP, through qPCR.
Perform single-cell RNA sequencing on additional tumor samples to validate these findings.
